# Tests

- Use Node built-in test runner: `import { test, describe } from 'node:test'`
- Use `node:assert/strict` for assertions
- Run via `npm test` (`node --import tsx/esm --test tests/**/*.spec.ts`)

## Style

- Test pure functions directly (key generation, XPath variants, ranking, dynamic value detection)
- Use small `ElementContext` fixtures — see `ctx()` helper pattern in `scanner.spec.ts`
- No browser/Playwright in unit tests unless explicitly adding integration tests

## Coverage focus

- XPath variant generation and scoring edge cases
- Generic testId disambiguation
- Relational XPath strategies
- Constants and denylist behavior
